text: Hello Bianca! Nice to meet you. How is your weekend going?
Hi! It's going well besides the rain. It's made me wuss out and I'm heading home early from the bars haha. How is yours?
I secretly love the rain. But I'm not sure many people feel the same haha
Where were you out tonight?
Hahaha. You're crazy. I find the rain depressing. Don't you get bummed out that you can't do things outside?
A point to make here. Notice that disagreement and differences can spark more lively conversation than when you just go along with what people say. Debate can cause good friction.
Fair point. But it makes the inside activities so much better. I like cooking on rainy days :)
So you're a chef? :) And what do you like to cook when it's raining?
Hahaha, I wouldn't say I'm a pro. But I can make a mean lentil soup
Okay, I'm mildly impressed ;)
Why thank you haha
Most women appreciate a man who has some cooking skills. Also shows that you could cook dinner for 2.

text: Yeah, I guess it's kind of the same as you. I haven't quite met someone that I click with

Are you looking for something specific? Dating, relationship, friends, fun?
This is a bold question. But in this case it's good to be forward.

So I guess relationships and dating?
What about you?
I guess if I'm honest with myself, I just got out of a relationship, and have been focusing on work
So dating, friends, and fun. I generally like meeting new people.
Good job being honest and upfront. At the very least, it's good to be courteous to others.

I think we might be on different pages in that case

Anyways, I hope that you find what you are looking for. You seem like a very nice person
Thank you. Same to you :)
It's always important to be cordial, especially when its not a match. Good job leaving things on a good note
So are you specifically looking for a relationship?
I would say that I am looking to meet someone special. I don't like to rush into things, but yeah, something more than casual dating
What about you?
Same
I don't go out with expectations for a relationship or not. I find it best when things just happen naturally
But I would say that it's my intent to meet some special :)
This is a good statement. When people are "looking" for a relationship, that can come off as needy.
Seems like we're on the same page then :)
Yeah :)
